isEqual

public boolean isEqual(String checkURI)
                throws CommunicationException
Description copied from class: NodeAddress
Checks whether a given server URI is functionally same as the URI defined here. A string matching is not enough to verify the functional equivalence. For example, NodeAddress.host can be an IP address in one place, while it is the equivalent hostname in the other.

Specified by:
isEqual in class NodeAddress
Parameters:
checkURI - A server URI
Returns:
true if the given URI is functionally the same as the node address here; false otherwise.
Throws:
CommunicationException - When there is an error in parsing the URI or some network-based resolution produces an error message
